📋Bank Management System – Requirements
🔹 1. Functional Requirements	
          (What the system should do)
           User login and authentication (Admin/Staff/Customer)
           Create and manage customer accounts
           Deposit and withdraw money
           Transfer funds between accounts
           Check account balance
Maintain transaction history
          Loan application and approval process
          Interest calculation for accounts/loans
          Generate reports (transactions, customer details)
🔹 2. Non-Functional Requirements
           (How the system should perform)
         Security: Data should be protected with passwords and encryption
         Performance: Fast processing of transactions
         Reliability: Accurate and error-free operations
         Scalability: Can handle many users/accounts
         Usability: Easy to use interface
         Availability: System should be available most of the time
🔹 3. Hardware Requirements
          Computer/Laptop
           Minimum 4 GB RAM
         Hard disk (at least 500 GB recommended)
         Internet connection (optional for basic project)
🔹 4. Software Requirements
       Operating System: Windows / Linux / macOS
        Programming Language: C++, Java, Python, etc.
       Database: MySQL / Oracle / SQLite
       IDE: Code::Blocks / VS Code / Eclipse / NetBeans
🔹 5. User Requirements
    Basic computer knowledge
   Login credentials to access the system
   Authorization based on role (admin, staff, user)

